>[Question]
>HOW DO YOU FIND THE MODE IN A LIST OF NUMBERS WHEN NONE OF THE 
>NUMBERS ARE THE SAME 
>
>EXAMPLE 17.47
>        2.55
>        20.57
>        15.26
>        3.58
>        14.41
>        2.17
>        12.65
>        15.45
>
>
>[Difficulty]
>THE MODE IS THE NUMBER THAT REPEATS ITSELF THE MOST IN THE LIST-BUT 
>WHAT IF NONE OF THE NUMBERS REPEAT
>
>[Thoughts]
>I AM TRYING TO HELP MY SON AND I AM LOST

Hi Mark,

The definition of mode doesn't say the mode 'repeats' itself.  It just
says the mode is the number that appears most often.  If all the
values appear just once, they're _all_ modes, since they all tie for
the greatest number of appearances. 

Does this help? 

